Personal Notes: After finishing Fallout 3, I thought I'd play this one right away. After a few weeks, I realized that I was burnt out on Fallout games so I took a 3 or 4 month break about 15 hours in. After picking it up again, I realized that it was a very good game. (at least when it wasn't crashing) Definitely the best Fallout game. Went for the Independent Ending, having all factions (minus BoS, of course) supporting me. I did have mods, but all were either for graphics or bug fixes.

Or better yet, it chose me considering I was more or less restricted to it by the end game's preset paths.
